        <h1>NoteRoom Privacy Policy</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="container">
        <p>At NoteRoom, we are committed to safeguarding your privacy and ensuring that your experience with our platform is both secure and beneficial. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, share, and protect your personal information when you access and use NoteRoom, a platform created by students for students. Please read this policy carefully to understand our practices regarding your information and how we handle it.</p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <h3>1.1 Personal Information</h3>
        <p>We collect personal information that you voluntarily provide when registering for or using NoteRoom. This may include, but is not limited to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Name</li>
            <li>Email Address</li>
            <li>Phone Number</li>
            <li>Academic Interests</li>
            <li>Any other details you provide in your profile or through the platform</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.2 Non-Personal Information</h3>
        <p>We also collect non-personally identifiable information that may include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> We collect details about the device you use to access NoteRoom, such as your device type, operating system, and browser type.</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We gather data on how you interact with NoteRoom, including pages viewed, time spent on the platform, features used, and links clicked.</li>
            <li><strong>Cookies and Tracking Technologies:</strong> We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to collect information about your browsing behavior and preferences. These tools help us personalize your experience and improve the platform.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <h3>2.1 Providing and Enhancing the Service</h3>
        <p>We use your information to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Personalization:</strong> Tailor the content and features of NoteRoom to match your academic interests and preferences.</li>
            <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Send updates, notifications, and provide technical support and other relevant communications regarding your use of the platform.</li>
            <li><strong>Feature Development:</strong> Use aggregated data to identify trends and develop new features that enhance your experience.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.2 Academic and Educational Insights</h3>
        <p>Your data helps us better understand how students engage with the platform, allowing us to optimize our services to better suit your educational needs. We may analyze usage patterns to improve the relevance of the content and resources available on NoteRoom.</p>

        <h2>3. Data Sharing with Third Parties</h2>
        <p>To support the development, maintenance, and future growth of NoteRoom, we may share certain non-personally identifiable information with third-party partners, including educational institutions and service providers. These partners may use this data to tailor their offerings to better match your academic and personal interests. This practice allows us to keep NoteRoom free and sustainable, ensuring that we can continue providing valuable tools to students.</p>

        <h3>3.1 Sharing with Educational Partners</h3>
        <p>We collaborate with third-party educational partners, such as tutoring services and academic resource providers, to deliver opportunities that align with your academic journey. The data shared is aggregated and anonymized, focusing on patterns and trends that help our partners develop content and services that are relevant to your needs.</p>

        <h3>3.2 Supporting NoteRoomâ€™s Sustainability</h3>
        <p>To maintain and continuously improve NoteRoom, economic assistance is important and can be reinvested into the platform. By partnering with third-party organizations, we secure the necessary funding to keep NoteRoom free for all users. These partnerships allow us to enhance the platformâ€™s features without compromising user privacy, as all shared data is anonymized to ensure your identity remains protected.</p>

        <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
        <h3>4.1 Protecting Your Information</h3>
        <p>We take data security seriously and implement industry-standard measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. Our security practices include encryption, secure data storage, and regular security audits to ensure your data is safe.</p>

        <h3>4.2 User Responsibilities</h3>
        <p>While we strive to protect your information, we also encourage you to take steps to safeguard your personal data. This includes using strong passwords, logging out after each session, and being cautious about sharing your login credentials.</p>

        <h2>5. User Control and Transparency</h2>
        <h3>5.1 Accessing and Managing Your Data</h3>
        <p>You have the right to access and manage your personal information through your account settings. This includes the ability to update, modify, or delete your data at any time. We believe in transparency and provide clear explanations of how your data is used and shared.</p>

        <h3>5.2 Opting Out of Data Sharing</h3>
        <p>If you prefer not to have your non-personally identifiable information shared with third-party partners, you can opt out through your account settings. Please note that opting out may limit certain features and personalized services available on NoteRoom.</p>

        <h2>6. Compliance with Legal Requirements</h2>
        <p>We are committed to complying with all relevant privacy laws and regulations. Our data practices are regularly reviewed to ensure they align with legal requirements and industry best practices. We take your privacy seriously and are dedicated to protecting your rights under applicable laws.</p>

        <h2>7. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
        <h3>Use of Cookies</h3>
        <p>Cookies are small data files stored on your device that help us enhance your experience on NoteRoom. We use cookies to remember your preferences, improve site performance, and gather usage statistics. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings.</p>

        <h2>8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, the platform, or legal requirements. Any significant changes will be communicated to you through the platform or via email. We encourage you to review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting your information.</p>

        <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding your privacy or this Privacy Policy, please contact us from the support page or at <a href="mailto:noteroom.support@gmail.com">noteroom.support@gmail.com</a>. We are committed to addressing your concerns and ensuring that your experience with NoteRoom is positive and secure.</p>
